.DevCSB Configuration: device configuration: Sound Blaster
[Configuration: device configuration: Sound Blaster]

  Most compatibles should work with the following sections and options aswell.
Be sure to include a mixing device aswell if you want to play module file types.

  \[devpSB\]
    link=devpSB
    sbrevstereo=off
    subtype= ; 1:sb 1.x, 2:sb 2.x, 3:sb pro, 4:sb16/32/64/awe

  \[devsSB\]
    link=devsSB
    sbrevstereo=off

  ~sbrevstereo~      some revisions of the Sound Blaster Pro (and clones) have a
                   bug when playing stereo. The right and left channels are
                   switched. To get the right order enable this option.
  ~subtype~          if your card is not properly detected (this can happen when
                   clones are not 100% compatible) you can set the type of card
                   with this option)

                     ~1~  normal mono SoundBlaster 22kHz 8bit
                     ~2~  SoundBlaster mono 44kHz 8bit
                     ~3~  SoundBlaster Pro either mono 44kHz 8bit
                                             or stereo 22kHz 8bit
                     ~4~  SoundBlaster 16+ stereo 44kHz 16bit

