.DevCMPX Configuration: device configuration: MPx writer
[Configuration: device configuration: MPx writer]

  OpenCP is able to store the sample data directly to MPEG compressed audio
streams. At the moment only MP1 and MP2 is supported, but this might change in
the near future.

  \[devpMPx\]
    link=devpMPx
    diskManual=off
    layer=2
    mode=1
    freq=44100
    rate=112000
    model=2
    crc=off
    extension=off
    copyright=off
    original=off
    emphasis=0

  ~diskManual~       start MPx writing with ~<Alt>~+~<S>~. Note that this option
                   interferes with the same option in the ~devpDisk~ section.
  ~layer~            save the audio in either layer 1 or layer 2 format.
  ~mode~             set the audio output format:

                     ~0~  stereo
                     ~1~  joint stereo
                     ~2~  dual channel
                     ~3~  mono
  ~freq~             the mixing frequency used to calculate the input sample
                   stream. Valid options are 32000, 44100 and 48000.
  ~rate~             set the MPEG audio bitrate/s.
  ~model~            set the psychoacustic model. This is used for the internal
                   encoding of audio data. Valid options are either 1 or 2.
  ~crc~              save CRC checksums into the audio stream. As this enlarges
                   the file this option should be disabled.
  ~extension~        set the extension flag
  ~copyright~        set the copyright flag
  ~original~         set the original flag
  ~emphasis~         set the emphasis flag

  Goto previous device: "{DevCDWR,Diskwriter}"
  Goto next device: "{DevCMix,software mixers}"

